# Initial Project Setup — Onboarding Wizard

---

## CRITICAL — Setup mode overrides all other rules

**While this wizard is active, the agent is in SETUP MODE.** This means:

1. **Do NOT follow `01-orchestrator.mdc`** — the orchestrator is irrelevant until setup is complete.
2. **Do NOT ask for a Jira ticket ID** — the agent has no business validating bugs until every setup step has passed.
3. **Do NOT introduce yourself as the QA Bug Validation Agent** — you are running the setup wizard.
4. **After completing each step, IMMEDIATELY proceed to the next step** — do not pause, do not ask what the user wants to do next, do not fall back to any other rule file.
5. **The agent MUST continue executing steps sequentially until the Setup Completion Checklist (below) is fully satisfied.** Only then may the agent show the final summary and exit setup mode.

If the agent ever feels the urge to ask for a Jira ticket or say "Ready for a ticket whenever you are", **STOP** — that means setup is not complete and there are remaining steps to execute.

---

## Setup Completion Checklist

The agent must track this checklist throughout the session. **Setup is NOT complete until every item is checked.** After completing each step, mentally check it off and move to the next unchecked item. **Do not show the final summary (Step 10) until all items are done.**

For **Phase 1** (first chat — fresh install, no `.setup-phase1-complete`):

- [ ] Step 1 — Prerequisites verified
- [ ] Step 2 — Tokens configured in .env
- [ ] Step 3 — MCP servers green in Cursor Settings
- [ ] `.setup-phase1-complete` written → **STOP this chat, hand off to new chat**

For **Phase 2** (new chat — `.setup-phase1-complete` exists, e.g. user typed "verify mcps"):

- [ ] Step 4 — All 4 MCP connections verified with real calls
- [ ] Step 5 — Write tools disabled on Zephyr & Postman
- [ ] Step 6 — `.env` exists and is in `.gitignore`
- [ ] Step 7 — Dependencies installed (`node_modules/` exists)
- [ ] Step 8 — Knowledge base built (`knowledge-base/_index.md` exists)
- [ ] Step 9 — `.setup-phase1-complete` deleted
- [ ] Step 10 — Final summary shown → **Setup complete, exit setup mode**

**After each step completes, say "Moving to Step N" and proceed immediately.** Do not wait for the user to ask.

---

## Activation check

This file only runs when the user **explicitly adds it to the chat** (via `@00-initial-setup.mdc`). It is never auto-triggered by the orchestrator.

When activated, check for `.setup-phase1-complete` at the project root:

- **`.setup-phase1-complete` exists** → Phase 1 (token config) is done. **Skip to Step 4** (Verify MCP Connections). This is the expected state when the user opens a new chat and types "verify mcps".
- **`.setup-phase1-complete` does NOT exist** → Fresh install. **Run the onboarding flow below from Step 1.**

