## STEP 5 — Disable Write Tools on Zephyr & Postman MCPs

Tell the user:

```
Disable write tools on Zephyr and Postman MCPs (safety — read-only access is all the agent needs):

  1. Cursor Settings → Tools & MCP
  2. Expand "user-zephyr-server" → toggle OFF any create/update/delete tools
     Keep enabled: get_test_case, get_test_execution, get_test_run, get_test_run_cases, search_test_cases_by_folder, search_test_runs
  3. Expand "user-postman_mcp_server" → toggle OFF any create/update/delete tools
     Keep enabled: getCollection, getCollections, getEnvironment, getEnvironments, getWorkspace, getWorkspaces, and other get/read tools
```

Then ask using **AskQuestion**:

```json
{
  "id": "write-tools-disabled",
  "prompt": "Have you disabled the write tools on Zephyr and Postman MCPs?",
  "options": [
    { "id": "done",      "label": "Yes — disabled" },
    { "id": "need-help", "label": "Need help" }
  ]
}
```

Wait for confirmation, then proceed.

**✅ Step 5 done → Immediately proceed to Step 6. Do NOT stop here.**

